<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='492000' id='t-492000'>middle-aged, former steelworker guy</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='494000' id='t-494000'>to watch their children at home,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='496000' id='t-496000'>and that would be good for the men, but that hasn't quite happened yet.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:30
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='499000' id='t-499000'>To see what's going to happen, you can't just look at the workforce that is now,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='502000' id='t-502000'>you have to look at our future workforce.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='505000' id='t-505000'>And here the story is fairly simple.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='508000' id='t-508000'>Women are getting college degrees</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='510000' id='t-510000'>at a faster rate than men.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='512000' id='t-512000'>Why? This is a real mystery.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='514000' id='t-514000'>People have asked men, why don't they just go back to college,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='517000' id='t-517000'>to community college, say, and retool themselves,</span>
