<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='534000' id='t-534000'>And what's even more disturbing</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='536000' id='t-536000'>is what's happening with younger boys.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='538000' id='t-538000'>There's been about a decade of research</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='540000' id='t-540000'>about what people are calling the &quot;boy crisis.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='542000' id='t-542000'>Now the boy crisis is this idea</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='544000' id='t-544000'>that very young boys, for whatever reason,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='547000' id='t-547000'>are doing worse in school than very young girls,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='550000' id='t-550000'>and people have theories about that.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='552000' id='t-552000'>Is it because we have an excessively verbal curriculum,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='554000' id='t-554000'>and little girls are better at that than little boys?</span>
